      • intersection

        public static Pair<Vect3,java.lang.Double> intersection(Vect3 so3,
                                                        Velocity vo3,
                                                        Vect3 si3,
                                                        Velocity vi3)
        Computes 2D intersection point of two lines, but also finds z component (projected by time from line 1) This z-component is constrained to be within the z components of the defining points.
        Parameters:
        s0 - starting point of line 1
        v0 - direction vector for line 1
        s1 - starting point of line 2
        v1 - direction vector of line 2
        Returns:
        Pair (2-dimensional point of intersection with 3D projection, relative time of intersection, relative to the so3) Note the intersection may be in the past. If the lines are parallel, this returns the pair (0,NaN).

      • distanceH

        public static double distanceH(Vect3 soA,
                               Vect3 soB)
        Given two lines defined by so, so2 and si, si2 return the intersection point Calculate altitude of intersection using the average of the altitudes of the two closests points to the intersection.
        Parameters:
        so1 - first point of line A
        so2 - second point of line A
        dto - the delta time between point so and point so2.
        si1 - first point of line B
        si2 - second point of line B
        Returns:
        a pair: intersection point and the delta time from point "so" to the intersection, can be negative if intersect point is in the past if intersection point is invalid then the returned delta time is -1

        public static double timeOfIntersection(Vect3 so3,
                                        Velocity vo3,
                                        Vect3 si3,
                                        Velocity vi3)
        Computes 2D intersection point of two lines, but also finds z component (projected by time from line 1)
        Parameters:
        s0 - starting point of line 1
        v0 - direction vector for line 1
        s1 - starting point of line 2
        v1 - direction vector of line 2
        Returns:
        time the OWNSHIP (so3) will reach the point. Note that the intruder (si3) may have already passed this point. If the lines are parallel, this returns NaN.
